
* allow *

Usage: allow <level>/all [ <user> ]

This command allows <user> to have <level> (for SAINTs or higher levels).
If an user has a level equal or greater than SAINT and the user not exists
in allow file, that user will be automatically demoted at first login time.

To see the list of allowed users for level <level>, type ".allow <level>"

To allow an user to all levels, use 'all' option.

See also: .dallow
 
